      <section>
         <p>All cables must comply with the national and/or electrical
code. The maximum allowable conductor size is 95 mm². Recommended
cables are based on table 52–C2 of IEC 60364–5–52
with the following assertions:</p>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <p>90 °C conductors</p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p>An ambient temperature of 30 °C</p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p>Use of flexible copper conductors</p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p>Installation method C</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p>If the ambient temperature is greater than 30 °C, larger
conductors are to be selected in accordance with the correction factors
of the IEC.</p>
